Package org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.cloudlet

The package provides CloudletScheduler implementations that are used to schedule the execution of multiple Cloudlet inside a given Vm.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CloudletScheduler
    An interface to be implemented by each class that provides a policy of scheduling performed by a virtual machine to run its Cloudlets.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CloudletSchedulerAbstract
    Implements the basic features of a CloudletScheduler, representing the policy of scheduling performed by a virtual machine to run its Cloudlets.
    CloudletSchedulerCompletelyFair
    A simplified implementation of the Completely Fair Scheduler (CFS) that is the default scheduler used for most tasks on recent Linux Kernel.
    CloudletSchedulerDynamicWorkload
    CloudletSchedulerDynamicWorkload implements a policy of scheduling performed by a virtual machine to run its Cloudlets, assuming there is just one cloudlet which is working as an online service.
    CloudletSchedulerSpaceShared
    CloudletSchedulerSpaceShared implements a policy of scheduling performed by a virtual machine to run its Cloudlets.
    CloudletSchedulerTimeShared
    CloudletSchedulerTimeShared implements a policy of scheduling performed by a virtual machine to run its Cloudlets.

Package org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.cloudlet Description

The package provides CloudletScheduler implementations that are used to schedule the execution of multiple Cloudlet inside a given Vm.

See the documentation of the package from the upper level for more details.
